1
00:00:03,170 --> 00:00:05,423
<i>Some people
have said I'm overly sensitive.</i>

2
00:00:10,594 --> 00:00:11,762
What now?

3
00:00:11,846 --> 00:00:14,223
Missy gave me cinnamon gum!

4
00:00:15,599 --> 00:00:18,394
Sure, sure.

5
00:00:18,477 --> 00:00:20,604
<i>And by some people,
I mean everyone.</i>

6
00:00:23,607 --> 00:00:25,007
<i>While I may not be</i>
X-Men <i>material...</i>

7
00:00:26,110 --> 00:00:29,405
<i>...I have always possessed
unusually heightened senses.</i>

8
00:00:29,488 --> 00:00:30,489
Ew.

9
00:00:31,157 --> 00:00:34,160
<i>Georgie,
put your shoes back on!</i>

10
00:00:34,243 --> 00:00:35,786
He can't smell this.

11
00:00:35,870 --> 00:00:37,329
<i>Yes, I can!</i>

12
00:00:37,413 --> 00:00:40,458
<i>I also had
extraordinary hearing.</i>

13
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:45,546
<i>During dinner, I could tune out
the cacophony of chewing,</i>

14
00:00:45,629 --> 00:00:47,298
<i>slurping,</i>

15
00:00:47,381 --> 00:00:51,927
<i>chewing, cutlery scraping
against plates,</i>

16
00:00:52,011 --> 00:00:53,679
<i>chewing,</i>

17
00:00:53,763 --> 00:00:55,014
<i>and my father's heavy breathing</i>

18
00:00:55,097 --> 00:00:56,537
<i>as he wrestled
with a ketchup bottle.</i>

19
00:00:59,477 --> 00:01:02,438
<i>But tonight, there was
one sound I couldn't tune out.</i>

20
00:01:07,026 --> 00:01:08,486
Why aren't you
eating, Sheldon?

21
00:01:08,569 --> 00:01:11,864
How can I with that
horrible noise?

22
00:01:11,947 --> 00:01:13,199
What noise?

23
00:01:13,282 --> 00:01:15,868
That irritating,
high-pitched buzz.

24
00:01:16,410 --> 00:01:17,495
I don't hear nothin'.

25
00:01:17,578 --> 00:01:18,662
Me, neither.

26
00:01:18,746 --> 00:01:20,414
How can you not?

27
00:01:20,498 --> 00:01:21,499
Wait.

28
00:01:21,582 --> 00:01:22,582
I think I hear it.

29
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:24,335
- You do?
- Yeah.

30
00:01:24,418 --> 00:01:26,253
It's coming out of your face.

31
00:01:29,799 --> 00:01:32,843
I guess I hear a little hum.

32
00:01:32,927 --> 00:01:34,720
Refrigerators make
noise, Sheldon.

33
00:01:34,804 --> 00:01:37,306
This is new. It's never
made this sound before.

34
00:01:37,389 --> 00:01:38,849
We should call a repairman.

35
00:01:38,933 --> 00:01:41,143
I'm not spending money
on a fridge that's workin'.

36
00:01:41,227 --> 00:01:43,938
Then think of it as spending
money on my mental stability.

37
00:01:44,021 --> 00:01:46,440
Ignore it, Sheldon.

38
00:01:47,191 --> 00:01:50,027
<i>Ignoring things that irritate
me isn't my strong suit.</i>

39
00:01:51,654 --> 00:01:53,280
<i>Obsessively fixating on them...</i>

40
00:01:53,364 --> 00:01:56,283
<i>now that's what gets me
out of bed in the morning.</i>

41
00:01:56,367 --> 00:01:59,203
<i>♪♪ Nobody else
is stronger than I am ♪♪</i>

42
00:01:59,286 --> 00:02:02,039
<i>♪♪ Yesterday I moved a mountain ♪♪</i>

43
00:02:02,123 --> 00:02:04,667
<i>♪♪ I bet I could be your hero ♪♪</i>

44
00:02:04,750 --> 00:02:07,002
<i>♪♪ I am a mighty little man ♪♪</i>

45
00:02:07,086 --> 00:02:11,215
<i>♪♪ I am a mighty little man. ♪♪</i>

46
00:02:19,974 --> 00:02:21,600
What are you doing?

47
00:02:21,684 --> 00:02:23,519
The sound from the refrigerator.

48
00:02:23,602 --> 00:02:25,896
It's right between D
and D-sharp.

49
00:02:25,980 --> 00:02:28,232
Ugh! It's making my skin crawl.

50
00:02:29,233 --> 00:02:30,734
What if I hold a pillow
over your face

51
00:02:30,818 --> 00:02:32,403
for, like, a really long time?

52
00:02:32,486 --> 00:02:34,029
No, that's dangerous.

53
00:02:35,030 --> 00:02:36,574
Do you know if we have earplugs?

54
00:02:36,657 --> 00:02:38,617
If we did,
I'd be wearing them.

55
00:02:38,701 --> 00:02:40,077
Go to sleep.

56
00:02:40,995 --> 00:02:42,705
I can't.

57
00:02:42,788 --> 00:02:44,957
Put your fingers in your ears.

58
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:47,751
And risk driving wax back
into my inner ear canal?

59
00:02:47,835 --> 00:02:48,836
No, thank you.

60
00:02:52,131 --> 00:02:54,091
Oh.

61
